Noninvasive positive pressure ventilation (NPPV) via nasal mask is well known to 
be effective in the treatment of acute respiratory failure (ARF) secondary to 
chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). A case of ARF with hypercapnic 
coma due to exacerbation of COPD is described. Six hours of conservative therapy 
with oxygen and medical treatment did not show any result. As endotracheal 
intubation (ET) was avoided on the basis of advanced age, poor life expectancy 
