Surgery without radiotherapy for primary treatment of endometrial cancer.

Larson DM(1), Broste SK, Krawisz BR.

Author information:
(1)Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology, Marshfield Clinic, Wisconsin, USA. 
larson@dgabby.mfldclin.edu

OBJECTIVE: To analyze the role of surgery alone, including pelvic and 
para-aortic lymphadenectomy, in patients with endometrial cancer who did not 
receive radiotherapy.
METHODS: Between August 1987 and January 1997, 225 women with disease clinically 
confined to the uterus were staged surgically by a standard protocol that 
